Helsinki's [[coat of arms]] first appeared on a 17th-century [[Seal (emblem)|seal]].<ref name="waymarking">{{cite web| url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WMTF04_Coat_of_arms_of_Helsinki_Finland | title=Coat of arms of Helsinki – Finland – Coats of Arms on Waymarking.com | website=www.waymarking.com | accessdate=15 October 2017 }}</ref> The current design was drawn by heraldist A. W. Rancken in 1951.{{fact|date=October 2017}} The [[blazon]] states: ”On a field azure, boat or on waves argent; crown or above the boat.”
