[[File:BoforsElma2.jpg|thumb|Elma ASW-600]] The '''Elma ASW-600''' is an [[anti-submarine warfare]] system designed by the [[Saab Group]] and used by the [[Royal Swedish Navy]]. It is designated in Antiubåts-granatkastarsystemen 83 in Sweden, and was previously called the Elma LLS-920.<ref name="IHS">{{cite news |url=http://www.janes.com/article/77987/sweden-to-reintroduce-asw-600-anti-submarine-grenade-launcher?from_rss=1 |title=Sweden to reintroduce ASW 600 anti-submarine grenade launcher |first=Richard |last=Scott |date=February 17, 2018 |publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]]}}</ref><ref name="Prezelin1995">{{cite book|author=Bernard Prezelin|title=The Naval Institute Guide to Combat Fleets of the World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qpU-AQAAIAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Naval Institute Press|page=701 |quote=ASW 600, the Malin small depth charge, and ASW 600 ASW rocket launcher (formerly named Elma LLS-920) are available for helicopter and surface-ship use.}}</ref>
==History== The ASW-600 was initially designed in the 1980s.<ref name="IHS"/> In 2018, the [[Defence Materiel Administration]] announced it would be reintroducing the system aboard [[Koster-class mine countermeasures vessel|''Koster''-class mine countermeasures vessels]].<ref name="IHS"/>
==Export== In 1993, the Swedish Parliamentary Advisory Council on the Export of War Materials approved the export of the ASW-600 to [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite news |quote=Apparently he had forgotten that just last year the Social Democrats cleared the sales of anti-submarine missiles (ASW-600) and timing devices for canons (EOS-400) to Indonesia. The permission for these deals was the work of three Social Democrats- Sture Ericson, Barbro Evermo-Palmerlund and Reynoldh Furustrand- in the Parliamentary Advisory Council on the Export of War Materials. |title=New Dirty Laundry on the Arms Front |first=Henrik |last=Westander |publisher=''[[Aftonbladet]]'' |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180219205227/https://www.library.ohio.edu/indopubs/1994/10/26/0004.html |archive-date=February 19, 2018 |url=https://www.library.ohio.edu/indopubs/1994/10/26/0004.html}}</ref>
