Colonel '''Necabettin Ergenekon''' (born 1926, in [[Erzurum]]) is a [[Turkish Army]] officer who retired in 1982, having been commander of the [[Turkish Gendarmerie]] in [[Adıyaman Province]] after the [[1980 Turkish coup d'état]]. Born ''Necabettin Baltacı'', he changed his name "some time in the '60s" to avoid confusion with another person by the same name.<ref name=Zaman/> At one time, Ergenekon was the commanding officer of [[Veli Küçük]].<ref>H. Akin Ünver (2009), "[http://dspace.cigilibrary.org/jspui/bitstream/123456789/27137/1/Turkeys%20Deep-State%20and%20the%20Ergenekon%20Conundrum.pdf?1 Turkey’s “Deep-State” and the Ergenekon Conundrum]", The Middle East Institute Policy Brief 23, April 2009</ref> Ergenekon was suspected by later-assassinated state prosecutor [[Cevat Yurdakul]] as being behind a string of mysterious deaths in the 70s, but no legal action was ever taken.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radikal.com.tr/Radikal.aspx?aType=RadikalHaberDetay&ArticleID=911847|accessdate=2008-12-27|title=Özel Harp Dairesi’nden Jitem’e|section=Radikal 2 |work=[[Radikal]]|date=2008-12-07|first=Ahmet|last=Insel|language=Turkish}}</ref> 

With the development of public discussion about the [[Ergenekon (organization)|Ergenekon organization]] in the 2000s, Ergenekon's name has sometimes been raised as a possible participant, possibly even responsible for its naming. Ergenekon rejects these allegations and says his name (chosen for the [[Ergenekon]] myth) has been besmirched by traitors.<ref name=Zaman>{{cite news|url=http://www.zaman.com.tr/haber.do?haberno=715853&title=veli-kucukun-komutani-ergenekon-vatan-hainleri-soyadimi-kirletti|accessdate=2008-11-19|title=Veli Küçük'ün komutanı Ergenekon: Vatan hainleri soyadımı kirletti|language=Turkish|date=2008-07-19|work=Zaman|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011041058/http://zaman.com.tr/haber.do?haberno=715853&title=veli-kucukun-komutani-ergenekon-vatan-hainleri-soyadimi-kirletti|archivedate=2008-10-11|df=}}</ref> Key [[Ergenekon trials]] witness [[Tuncay Güney]] claims Ergenekon introduced him to [[Veli Küçük]], a key defendant in the trials. Güney also alleged that Ergenekon had had discussions with [[Recep Tayyip Erdoğan]] in the 1980s.<ref>yenicaggazetesi.com.tr, [http://www.yenicaggazetesi.com.tr/yeni/haberdetay.php?hit=12496 GÖZDEN KAÇAN AYRINTI]</ref> In December 2008 ''[[Yeni Şafak]]'' claimed that Ergenekon had led the [[1995 Azeri coup d'état attempt]], which had support from elements in Turkey.<ref>[[Today's Zaman]], 17 December 2008, [http://todayszaman.com/news-161485-report-garihs-execution-warrant-issued-in-1995.html Report: Garih’s execution warrant issued in 1995]</ref><ref>''[[Yeni Şafak]]'', 24 December 2008, [http://yenisafak.com.tr/Gundem/?t=24.12.2008&i=156509 Üzeyir Garih'in ipi Aliyev'e darbe planında çekildi]</ref>

