'''Bishop Stephen Fennelly''' DD (1816 &ndash; 1880)  was an Irish born [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Madras and Mylapore|Roman Catholic Bishop of Madras]] in India from 1868 until 1880. Dr. Fennelly was from [[Moyne, County Tipperary,]],  he succeeded his brother Rev. Dr. [[John Fennelly]] who had served as Bishop of Madras from 1841 until his death 1868.  He served as Vicar General for the Diocese of Madras, he also gained the religious title of Monsignor. He brought the Irish Patrician Brothers to India in 1875.<ref>[http://patricianbrothersindia.com/home/history History] Patrician Brothers</ref>

