'''Zokela''' is a musical group from the [[Central African Republic]], one of the most influential in the country. The group are responsible for a style of African music of the same name which emerged in the early 1980s.<ref name="Shepherd2005">{{cite book|author=John Shepherd|title=Continuum encyclopedia of popular music of the world|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jhUKAQAAMAAJ|year=2005|publisher=Continuum|isbn=978-0-8264-7436-0|page=264}}</ref>
The [[Bangui]]-based band features electric guitars and drums with the "insistent and vital sound of ceremonies and funeral dances of the [[Lobaye]]".<ref name="Kisliuk1998">{{cite book|author=Michelle Robin Kisliuk|title=Seize the Dance!: BaAka Musical Life and the Ethnography of Performance|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wo0qwaGbkgoC&pg=PA182|year=1998|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-514404-8|page=182}}</ref>

